description: A harried Yoichi Taba finally receives a long overdue day off. However, his vacation is short-lived when he runs into Kagura Security member Eiko Rando, who desperately needs his help on a case. He grudgingly agrees - but soon regrets it - as she leads him into the sewers of Tokyo. He finds that computer geek Eiko is just as careless as the rest of the Kagura girls? and that he¹s in for another night he¹ll never forget!

Continuing their battles against the threat of Phantom Cats, the Kagura Security Agency heads to the local underground mall to meet the demons head on. There, they run afoul of the police, who don't take kindly to Kagura's methods and weapons. Escaping custody, Yoichi runs right into the Black Cat, master of the phantom felines! With all his backup on their way to jail, it's up to him to tackle the ringleader alone!

In this issue, we meet Yu Himehagi, a professional driver, fallen on hard times, now in the employ of Kagura Security. And who better to call when a cat demon has taken control of a tractor trailer and is terrorizing the highways of Tokyo?! Yoichi and Yuka have to hold onto their hats as they are in for the ride of their lives. It seems Himehagi does not know the meaning of the word brakes, and the other motorists best get off the road. This is one of the wildest high-speed chases you¹ve ever seen!

Kicking off an all new storyline! The first six issues of Geobreeders served as individual introductions to the characters, but now we see how they work together as a team. As Taba and Takami relax on a rainy afternoon, they are visited by the mysterious young girl who has been following them. The young girl is indeed a cat phantom, but is she friend or foe? The answer to that question draws the Kagura Security team into a finely woven web of mystery and intrigue that starts right here!

More of the mysteries surrounding the Society of Phantom Cats come to light. The threat is even bigger than Kagura even thought, and their latest job goes to prove it. In their biggest undertaking yet, the whole team is mobilized as an unconfirmed number of Phantom Cats take over a construction site. Action, action, action this month!! And just who is the mysterious Mr. Irie of the Ministry of Welfare and why is he so interested in Kagura and Yoichi Taba?

Yoichi and Takami hold down the fort at Kagura Security as Yuka and the rest of the Kagura ladies travel to a secluded spa for a little R&R. When a Phantom Cat rears its ugly head, will the efforts of the sole pair of Kagura Detectives be enough to defeat it? And will Yuka, Maki, and Eiko be able to keep themselves from killing each other?

Jet skis, boats, bikinis... sounds like a great way to spend one of your days off enjoying some fun in the sun, right? Until your party is crashed by the Kagura Security agents, that is! Looks like the Phantom Cats are one group of felines that aren't afraid of the water, and Yoichi and the lovely ladies find out the hard way! In a boat chase John Woo would be proud of, bullets and bikinis fly as the waterways around Tokyo become a battlefield.
The phone rings, and killer-for-hire Harvey embarks on another hit. But nothing’s going right this job. There’s little room for error in the business of killing – so what happens when one occurs?
name: Imagine Me

description: Harvey is a contract killer who surfaces only to cap fools and get paid... a ghost cutting a bloody swath through the living world, invisible and therefore untouchable. But now, the ghost is being haunted by someone from the real world... a woman whom Harvey simply can't get out of his head ... a woman who's made Harvey so damn crazy he just might decide that living is worth the risk of dying.
name: Cold

volume.name: Samuree Mistress of the Martial Arts

name: Samuree Mistress of the Martial Arts

description:
In Chimney25 by Nightmares and Fairy Tales artist FSc, a giant Santa Claus piñata terrorizes a city, an alien races a boy for a chance to meet the Fairy Santa, and a lonely man receives an unexpected package.

A collection of Christmas-themed short graphic works, pin-ups and prose pieces.
name: Chimney 25

description: Collecting the first four issues of the series that Multiversity Comics says is 'Crafted so perfectly that it made me smile to no end.' When the Li'l Depressed Boy meets a strange girl, she drags him from his self-seclusion into a world of style points bowling, zombie fighting, laser tag battles, punk rock concerts and house parties. What will he do to learn her name? What will be her perfect birthday gift? How do you eat fried rice without chopsticks?
name: Volume One

volume.name: The Li'l Depressed Boy: She is Staggering

description:
In the latest issue of the way-out miniseries, Garbage Man flings a Dino-man by the tail, while Tanga tears off a piece of Za – the despot, that is, not the food! Plus: the origin of Robotman!

Robotman: Uncanny Valley Part 4- Robotman and Maddy Rouge are are hot on the trail of Dr. Turing, and the only thing between them an answers is a giant, nano-virus infected monster. While Robotman repairs the damage from being tossed like a rag doll by the latest monster, Maddy makes a dash for a bunker. While repairing Robotman thinks back to the accident that transformed him from flesh and blood to the metal hero he is today.

Garbage Man: Dream Monsters-Garbage Man fights off a dinosaur like lizard in the sewer, only to learn that the monster appears whenever one of Reverends congregation members falls asleep. Garbage Man, also thinks that this man the Reverend is describing may a victim of the same evil scientist that made him. The Reverend and Garbage Man's discussion is cut short when he hears Samantha yelling for help. The two are in time to save Samantha and some other homeless people for a second monster attack. When Garbage Man kills this one, a homeless man appears from the shadow begging Garbage Man to kill him before he creates an other monster. Meanwhile, Charles Haden is murdered.
name: Uncanny Valley, Part 4; Dream Monsters; Besieged

description: It's all aboard for action and danger for the Kagura Security agents as they tangle with the gang of Phantom Cats led by the mysterious and sinister Black Cat. It's round two of an all-out, sea-borne battle as bikini-clad, jet ski-riding agents Umezaki and Kikushima get caught in the crossfire between the Ministry of Welfare, the Phantom Cats, and the Navy. Action and laughter combine when the waterways around Tokyo are filled with babes, bazookas, and battleships, blasting away at each other with abandon!

Is this the end of the Kagura Security Agency? It's the most action-packed issue yet, as the Navy and the Ministry of Welfare blast boats and cars out from under Ms. Takami and her crew in an all-out battle in the waterways around Tokyo! And when they finally get to shore, what's facing them is one heck of a big tank.

The wacky supernatural-fighting professionals of the Kagura Security Agency have been recruited by the police to take on some flesh-and-blood opponents - but they're driving gigantic tanks! The bazooka-blasting agent babes are up to the task, but what happens when the Ministry of Welfare sends the Hounds after our heroines?

The wacky supernatural-fighting professionals of the Kagura Security Agency are up against opponents using gigantic tanks, and their tiny van seems likely to be crushed until they fool their opponents into driving off a building. Unfortunately, they have to drive off first! And what greets them on the ground but another Phantom Cat!

In this installment, the wide-eyed supernatural girl, Maya, learns how to cook spaghetti - with disastrous results! Also, the gang sets to go on their first vacation in years, getting them into a different kind of hot water!

The gorgeous ladies of the Kagura Security Agency are finally going to take a well- deserved vacation from battling supernatural menaces. But of course, they're not going to enjoy their time off for very long! In the first of a series of vacation stories, the gorgeous Eiko Rando goes home, and tries to relax with her family. She looks great in a kimono, but her idyllic visit is cut short when the Phantom Cats come calling, and it's martial arts action and magical spells flying until the supernaturals are defeated!

You might think things are going to get quiet when the crew of gorgeous, supernatural-fighting female professionals from the Kagura Security Agency finally take well-deserved vacations. It's Yu Himehagi's turn for some relaxation in this issue, and all she can do is relax - all she does is sleep! After a couple of days of this, her family decides to have some fun with her, and they put her in costume while she's asleep, as - what else? - a cat! All heck breaks loose when Yu finds out what they've done in one of the funniest Geobreeders issues yet!

She's tall, she's gorgeous, she dresses like Tom Wolfe (hat and white suit), and talks like Clint Eastwood! She's Maki Yumezaki, and she's off on a busman's holiday. You might think things are going to get quiet when the crew of gorgeous, supernatural-fighting female professionals from the Kagura Security Agency finally take well-deserved vacations. But Maki can't stay away from the action, and when she goes back to visit Takiori Enterprises, her old detective agency, it's gun-blazing action when she and her old compatriots tangle with the Suzuboshi gang. Geobreeders is the funniest, craziest, wildest Hong- Kong action-type comic around!

You might think things are going to get quiet when the crew of gorgeous, supernatural-fighting female professionals from the Kagura Security Agency finally take well-deserved vacations. But when the lanky and gorgeous Maki Yumezaki (who dresses like Tom Wolfe and talks like Clint Eastwood) visits her old detective agency, it's time for gun-blazing action! She and her old compatriots tangle with the Suzuboshi gang, and get involved in a pulse-pounding caper involving bags of cash and stolen diamonds. Talk about a working holiday! Geobreeders is the funniest, craziest, wildest Hong-Kong action-type comic around!

Lucien Gates is doing his best to adapt to his new powers and heroic identity as The Ray – but between giant monsters attacking San Diego and meeting his girlfriend's strict parents, things are not going so well. Someone is definitely behind these attacks and perhaps even Lucien's gaining his abilities. He'd better hope he can solve that mystery before his life is completely ruined.
name: Part Two

description: Geobreeders is the funniest, craziest, wildest Hong-Kong action-type comic around, with the gorgeous, outrageous women of the Kagura Security Agency fighting supernatural forces led by the mysterious Black Cat! The girls have been on vacation, but the fun's over when Japanese National Airlines taps them to stop a hijacking, and who's behind it but none other than the Black Cat! And is one of the girls trapped on the plane?! Soon the skies are filled with pursuing planes.

"Hydrology," the first arc of the critically acclaimed new BATWOMAN series, reaches its powerful conclusion! After the horrors Batwoman has faced, she has a final showdown with The Weeping Woman – a specter with the power to dredge up Kate's deepest pain. Can she finally forgive herself so she can dispel this evil? And how will she respond when Chase and the DEO tighten their grip, forcing Kate to make an impossible decision?
name: Hydrology, Part 5: Evapotranspiration

description:
Cover: Steve Yeowell (Nikolai Dante)

  • Judge Dredd - Day of Chaos - Eve of Destruction (part 1) (John Wagner - Henry Flint)
  • Grey Area - Meet and Greet (part 3) (Dan Abnett - Karl Richardson)
  • Nikolai Dante - The Wedding of Jena Makarov (part 3) (Robbie Morrison - Simon Fraser)
  • Absalom - Ghosts of London (part 1) (Gordon Rennie - Tiernen Trevallion)
  • Strontium Dog - The Life and Death of Johnny Alpha - Chapter Two: The Project (part 3) (John Wagner - Carlos and Hector Ezquerra)
name: Prog 1765

description: Terrorists in the skies over Tokyo? Highjackers joining forces with Phantom Cats? The gorgeous Geobreeders girls and the hapless Mr. Taba fly into action again as the Kagura Security team sets out to foil a hijacking for Japan National Airlines! Geobreeders is the funniest, craziest, wildest Hong-Kong action-type comic around, and things never seem to work out quite the way the girls have planned it! The skies over Tokyo are filled with pursuing planes and Eiko nearly meets her end as missiles fly and the harbor's container port collapses all around her! It's like a cross between Buffy and the X-Files, with a beautiful team of super-heroines and loads of supernatural action!

In this issue, the highjacker lands the Japan Airlines plane in the middle of Tokyo, and the gorgeous women of Kagura Security chase him through the streets of the city in the company vans! They're outgunned and outrun, until the Air Force sends interceptors into the fray! You haven't seen anything else in comics like the Kagura girls leaping to board a plane roaring through Tokyo. Geobreeders is like a cross between Buffy and The X-Files, with a beautiful team of super-heroines and loads of supernatural action!

It's another quiet day's work for the gorgeous, sexy women of Kagura Security. Dealing with an airplane highjacker, of course, is just all in a day's work for these girls. So what if the highjacker lands and takes off several times on the streets of Tokyo in his highjacked jumbo jet?! It barely musses their hair!

It's like a cross between Die Hard 2 and the hilarious movie Airplane when the gorgeous, sexy women of Kagura Security take on an airplane highjacker, who's bounced the highjacked jumbo jet up and down into the streets of Tokyo a couple of times before finally landing it in Ayagane harbor -- nose down! It's madness inside the downed plane, as the hot and hot-headed Kagura girls try to capture the highjacker while fighting off supernatural phantom cats!

The gorgeous, sexy women of Kagura Security try to relax after foiling an airplane highjacker, but leave it to Maki Yumezaki, the tall blonde girl who dresses like Tom Wolfe and talks like Clint Eastwood, to stir things up when she brings by a few samples from a friend's company. Her friend's in the weapons business, and soon the Kagura women are blasting away, much to the consternation of the hapless Mr. Taba. Meanwhile, other arms deals are going on, as the sinister minion of the Ministry of Welfare makes plans to get some dangerous new equipment.

Nobody loves a nice, big, hot weapon more than the gorgeous sexy women of Kagura Security and when Maki brings by a few samples from a friend's arms company, it's time to try out the merchandise. While the Kagura girls are having fun blasting their own offices, their supernatural friend, Phantom Cat Girl Maya, is in deep trouble, getting chased through Tokyo streets by her old compatriots. Mr. Taba and the team get to give their new toys a real workout when they go to her rescue. Geobreeders is a cross between Sailor Moon and The X-Files, with a beautiful team of super-heroines who are ready to spring into action to keep the world safe from supernatural evil, and who investigate the dark and mysterious forces that menace the modern world.

name: In der Holle der Tosenden Wasser

description: It's a full frontal assault by the gorgeous Kagura Security women when their dear friend, and the only supernatural being who's trying to help the human race, gets targeted by her old pals. Phantom Cat Girl Maya is in deep trouble, and who's she gonna call?? Why Mr. Taba and the all-girl detective team! Geobreeders is like a cross between Sailor Moon and The X-Files, with a beautiful team of action heroines who are ready to spring into action to keep the world safe from supernatural evil. And is there a new mastermind behind the Phantom Cats? Yes, it looks like the highjacker who nearly destroyed Tokyo is the one leading the assault on Maya!

Fans who love Merle the Cat-Girl from Esacaflowne will love Maya, the Phantom Cat Girl, from Geobreeders. This is Maya's story arc, and she's the damsel in distress who gets saved by a whole gang of other damsels (or gunsels?), the women of Kagura Security! Geobreeders is a fun and action-packed book with gorgeous heroines, wise- cracking, sharp-shooting female detectives who take on bad guys and bad ghouls with equal aplomb. One part X-Files (the supernaturals are part of government and corporate conspiracies), one part Buffy (or maybe four parts if you count all the beautiful Kagura girls!), and one part John Woo movies for action, Geobreeders is like nothing else in comics - fun, exciting and fabulously action-filled.

The gorgeous Kagura girls look just as good when they're snow bunnies as when they go to the beach! There's action in the ski lodge and on the slopes as they head for an alpine resort to chase the evil supernatural Phantom Cats! And they're good at shooting wrongdoers from snowmobiles as well as jet skis!

Cole and his new partner Sofia make plans to escape the northwest, but first they need a little cash – and that calls for a quick grift. Cole can't get far in his con-artistry, however, before discovering that the Daemonites are coming after him in full force – and they have powers he could not have anticipated.
name: The Sleep in Seattle

description: "The Icelandic Trilogy", continues with part 6 of 9, titled "Commerce." Where once the Haukssons lived a frontier life, conquering lands with sword and shield, the twin siblings who now carry the name conquer their enemies with money and influence. As the entire nation undergoes a huge cultural shift, can the Hauksson bloodline survive?
name: The Icelandic Trilogy, Part Six: Commerce 1000
Ten Ever-Lovin' Blue-Eyed Years With Pogo

volume.name: Ten Ever-Lovin' Blue-Eyed Years With Pogo

description: Recovered and recharged, Tom is ready to invade the cabal's inner sanctum as "Tommy Taylor and the War of Words" continues. And the Cabal are more than ready to receive him into the charged narrative space of the Grid. As Pullman's trap closes, revelations about the Cabal's true aims come thick and fast.
name: Part Three of Tommy Taylor and the War of Words

description: In this final PREACHER hardcover, Jesse Custer makes amends with his girlfriend, Tulip, then seeks revenge against his former friend and compatriot Cassidy for the things the Irish vampire did to her when they both believed the Preacher to be dead. Collecting #55-66 plus the special PREACHER: TALL IN THE SADDLE .
name: Book Six

description: In this new title collecting issues #25-30, Tom heads to New York, where the worldly goods of Wilson Taylor are being auctioned off – and the only thing more dangerous than the other bidders is the auctioneer. Then, Tom goes to extreme measures to learn about his father's activities in the Golden Age of comic books!
name: Volume 5

description: messy serie, first issue cover named hybrids special revengers, from 2 to 5 hybrids, the origin

“Cobra Command,” Part Two! Snake Eyes travels halfway around the world with his team to stop the invasion of a sovereign nation under attack by Cobra. But the Joes’ silent warrior may be on a mission all his own. Snake Eyes is haunted by his past and Storm Shadow is at the heart of it. Snake Eyes carves himself his own bloody corner in a war of annihilation!
name: Cobra Command Part 2
